cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS

This paper deals with the problem of generating monotonic surfaces, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of Markov chains and mixing time analysis suggests that it could also be classified under graph theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). The application of geometric distance functions and path coupling techniques is relevant to the field of computational geometry and topology (cs.SI). Finally, the study of fluctuating bias and its effect on the mixing time is related to the area of randomized algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
